I never thought I could love a dog THIS much and then Milo came into my life almost 7 years ago. I will do just about anything for him. Indies are extremely special : they are hardy which means they barely have any health issues, they’re loving, yet independent , friendly - the perfect family dog ( to the point where Milo will go home with anybody 🙄) , highly intelligent because they are survivors and they can be easily trained - but most of all,  they are in desperate need of homes. If you’re thinking of getting a dog , don’t think twice and just get an indie - I promise you will not regret it.

Never thought Id be here showing my pits to the internet, but here we are 🤷🏽‍♀️
This is approx 3 weeks of growth ( considering I also did laser)
Anyway, I used the @veetindia waxing strips. They come in handy because you can cut to whatever size you like and use it anywhere and LETS BE HONEST theres nothing more satisfying than getting that hair from the root. Waxing also removes the dead skin which I love so everything feels smooth and cleannn. I also use a clay mask after to cool down my skin because armpits need love too ok

I feel like getting a haircut that you’re genuinely happy with doesn’t happen very often. We’ve all had that haircut where instead of 1 inch, 6 inches were “ accidently” chopped off, and you end up looking like lord farquad , or the haircut expectation vs reality is v different and then you go home and have a little mental breakdown. But this is what I ask for each time I get my hair cut and the one person that truly gets it and is so good at his craft is @dwyessh_hairwizard 
 I forgot to take a “before” clip but I have hair that is thick and grows quickly, so you would think it would look nice if I left it open but it doesn’t , it just feels heavy and poofy and only looks good if I style it ( and lets be honest – hair styling is not my thing , I find it boring and tedious ) This is where a good haircut comes in . I like to keep the length but get the front parts in layers to remove the “thickness” but add volume , so I can leave it open. Even if I air dry it I’m good to go.
